<subSubSection id="C33611EEFFB5B45CFF6C78DEBD430617" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B934265FFB5B45CFF6C78DEBD430617" blockId="18.[151,1436,438,787]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="B9589E77FFB5B45CFF6C78DEBE5A05E2" bold="true" box="[151,266,438,463]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(based on 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD3F94FFB5B45CFE7E78DEBD0D05E2" author="Chani-Posse" box="[389,605,438,463]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" refString="Chani-Posse, M. (2010) Revision of the southern South American species of Philonthus Stephens (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Zootaxa, 2595, 1 - 70." type="journal article" year="2010">
Chani-Posse, 
<number id="3DE45042FFB5B45CFDDB78DFBD0D05E2" box="[544,605,439,463]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C39E6FFB5B45CFD9478DEBC3F05E3" box="[623,879,438,462]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Philonthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis id="B9589E77FFB5B45CFD9478DEBC3F05E3" box="[623,879,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Philonthus longicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be identified by the eyes about as long as to slightly longer than temples, the antennal segment 
<number id="3DE45042FFB5B45CFD2B78B3BD8E05DE" box="[720,734,475,499]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" value="2.0">2</number>
shorter than preceding segment and antennal segments 
<number id="3DE45042FFB5B45CFAB578B3BACC05DE" box="[1358,1436,475,499]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" value="7.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="4.0">4 to 10</number>
elongate, the dorsal rows of pronotum each with five punctures and the paramere shifted toward right margin of median lobe. Length 
<number id="3DE45042FFB5B45CFE7E7B4ABEF70616" box="[389,423,546,571]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" value="6.5">6.5</number>
–7.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33611EEFFB5B45CFF3C7B2EBCE5073E" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B934265FFB5B45CFF3C7B2EBDD306AE" blockId="18.[151,1436,438,787]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="B9589E77FFB5B45CFF3C7B2EBE300672" bold="true" box="[199,352,582,607]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2C39E6FFB5B45CFE977B2EBD210673" box="[364,625,582,606]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Philonthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis id="B9589E77FFB5B45CFE977B2EBD210673" box="[364,625,582,606]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Philonthus longicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently considered a cosmopolitan species widely distributed in Central and South 
<collectingCountry id="F33B02F5FFB5B45CFE937B02BE9806AE" box="[360,456,618,643]" name="United States of America" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">America</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD3F94FFB5B45CFE2C7B03BD2606AE" author="Herman" box="[471,630,619,643]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" refString="Herman, L. H. (2001) Catalog of the Staphylinidae (Insecta: Coleoptera). 1758 to the end of the second millennium. Part V. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 265, 2441 - 3020." type="journal article" year="2001">
Herman 
<number id="3DE45042FFB5B45CFDC17B03BD2606AE" box="[570,630,619,643]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B934265FFB5B45CFF3C7BE6BCE5073E" blockId="18.[151,1436,438,787]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="B9589E77FFB5B45CFF3C7BE6BE1A068A" bold="true" box="[199,330,654,679]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Bionomics.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2C39E6FFB5B45CFEAD7BE6BD0B068B" box="[342,603,654,678]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Philonthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis id="B9589E77FFB5B45CFEAD7BE6BD0B068B" box="[342,603,654,678]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Philonthus longicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been frequently found in cattle manure in open pastures of North 
<collectingCountry id="F33B02F5FFB5B45CFF6C7BDABFA706E6" box="[151,247,690,715]" name="United States of America" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">America</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD3F94FFB5B45CFEFC7BDBBE8406E6" author="Hu" box="[263,468,690,715]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" refString="Hu, G. Y. &amp; Frank, J. H. (1997) Predation on the horn fly (Diptera: Muscidae) by five species of Philonthus (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Environmental Entomology, 26, 1240 - 1246." type="journal article" year="1997">
Hu &amp; Frank 
<number id="3DE45042FFB5B45CFE607BDBBE8406E6" box="[411,468,691,715]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="F33B02F5FFB5B45CFDEE7BDABDD506E6" box="[533,645,690,715]" name="Argentina" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD3F94FFB5B45CFD6E7BDABC3706E6" author="Chani-Posse" box="[661,871,690,715]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" refString="Chani-Posse, M. R. (2004) Eight Argentinean species of dung-inhabiting Philonthus Stephens (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Studies on Neotropical Fauna and Environment, 39, 217 - 232. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 01650520412331271738" type="journal article" year="2004">
Chani-Posse 
<number id="3DE45042FFB5B45CFCD07BDBBC3706E6" box="[811,871,691,715]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), and also cited from other organic debris such as decaying plants, other animal droppings, carcasses, etc (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD3F94FFB5B45CFCEF7BBFBCEB06C2" author="Smetana" box="[788,955,726,751]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" refString="Smetana, A. (1995) Rove beetles of the subtribe Philonthina of America north of Mexico (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae): Classification, phylogeny and taxonomic revision. Memoirs on Entomology, International, 3, 1 - 946." type="journal article" year="1995">
Smetana 
<number id="3DE45042FFB5B45CFC847BBEBCEB06C2" box="[895,955,726,751]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This species was also collected from pig carcasses in arid environment of 
<collectingCountry id="F33B02F5FFB5B45CFDF37B92BD27073E" box="[520,631,762,787]" name="Argentina" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD3F94FFB5B45CFD7D7B92BC31073E" author="Aballay" box="[646,865,762,787]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" refString="Aballay, F. H., Murua, A. F., Acosta, J. C. &amp; Centeno, N. (2008) Primer registro de artropodofauna cadaverica en sustratos humanos y animales en San Juan, Argentina. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 67, 157 - 163." type="journal article" year="2008">
Aballay 
<emphasis id="B9589E77FFB5B45CFD1C7B93BC49073E" box="[743,793,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 2012).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
